All those instructions are tested to work on Ubuntu 16.04

1.install python 3.5, mysql, mysql-workbench, imagemagick and wand on your machine
$ sudo apt-get install python3-wand

2.navigate into the project folder 'photo_browse', and create a virtual environment
$ python3 -m venv flask

3.activate the venv
$ source flask/bin/activate

4.install flask, wand(an ImageMagick binding for python), and mysql-connector-python, boto3, gunicorn
$ flask/bin/pip3 install flask
$ flask/bin/pip3 install wand
$ flask/bin/pip3 install mysql-connector-python-rf --egg

5.use mysql-workbench to run sql script 'photo_browser_sql.sql', creating a database for use

6.change the value of 'password' in app/config.py to your mysql password

7.run
$ python3 run.py



